Data Acquisition Guide
This project uses physiological signal data from PhysioNet, a free and open repository of biomedical research data maintained by MIT.

Dataset
Name: Sleep Apnea Database (or equivalent multi-channel respiratory/oximetry dataset)
Source: https://physionet.org/
License: PhysioNet Credentialed Health Data License — free for research use
Format: WFDB (WaveForm DataBase) — binary signal files (.dat) + header files (.hea) + annotation files (.apn)

Step-by-Step Instructions
Option A: Download via browser

Go to https://physionet.org/content/apnea-ecg/ (or search PhysioNet for your specific dataset)
Create a free PhysioNet account if you don't have one
Click "Files" on the dataset page
Download the full dataset as a .zip or download individual records
Extract files into data/raw/ in this repository

Option B: Download via command line (recommended)
Install the PhysioNet client tool:
bashpip install wfdb
Then download directly in Python:
pythonimport wfdb

# Download all records for a dataset
wfdb.dl_database('apnea-ecg', dl_dir='data/raw/')
Or download a single record:
pythonwfdb.dl_record('apnea-ecg/a01', dl_dir='data/raw/')
Option C: Download via wget
bashwget -r -N -c -np https://physionet.org/files/apnea-ecg/1.0.0/ -P data/raw/

Expected File Structure
After downloading, data/raw/ should contain files like:
data/raw/
├── a01.dat       # Signal data (binary)
├── a01.hea       # Header (sampling rate, channel names, etc.)
├── a01.apn       # Apnea annotations (per-minute labels)
├── a02.dat
├── a02.hea
├── a02.apn
├── ...
└── RECORDS       # List of all record names
Each record corresponds to one subject's overnight recording. The .apn annotation file contains per-minute labels: A (apnea) or N (normal).

Verifying the Download
Run the following to confirm the data loaded correctly:
pythonimport wfdb

record = wfdb.rdrecord('data/raw/a01')
annotation = wfdb.rdann('data/raw/a01', 'apn')

print(record.sig_name)     # ['SaO2', 'RESP', ...]
print(record.fs)           # Sampling frequency
print(annotation.symbol)   # ['N', 'A', 'N', ...]

Signal Channels Used
This project uses two channels from each recording:
ChannelDescriptionSaO2 / SpO2Peripheral oxygen saturation (oximetry)RESPRespiratory effort signal
Other channels present in the dataset (e.g., ECG, EEG) are not used and can be ignored.

Notes

Do not commit data files to Git. The data/ directory is listed in .gitignore. Signal files are large and subject to PhysioNet's terms of use.
Account required for some datasets. Most PhysioNet datasets are open-access, but a small number require credentialing. Check the dataset page for access requirements.
Sampling rates vary by record. The loader in src/loader.py handles resampling automatically.
